{"type":"message","id":"1dee5ac2","parentId":"1210e720","timestamp":"2026-03-24T00:41:19.601Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The pulse ran successfully. The newest log file is `pulse_2026-03-23 203040.md`. Wait, actually the command listed the NEWEST file, but it says `pulse_2026-03-23 203040.md`... but the pulse output created `pulse_2026-03-23 204042.md`. Let me re-read - the pulse script created a new session file `pulse_2026-03-23 204042.md` and also a mutation file. The command output shows the newest file is `pulse_2026-03-23 203040.md`. That seems odd - maybe the 204042 one was just created and the Get-ChildItem ran before it showed up? Let me read the most recent one, which seems to be `pulse_2026-03-23 203040.md` based on the exec output, but actually the pulse output itself says it created `pulse_2026-03-23 204042.md`. \n\nThe timing is confusing me here - the pulse finished and reported creating `pulse_2026-03-23 204042.md`, but the file listing is showing `pulse_2026-03-23 203040.md` as the newest. Let me just read that file and see what's actually in it.","thinkingSignature":"a173dc109e995bf1fa9f40ee4bc629e3a9353b6e8e9e67d4a298dd3d3f3a8e7f"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_vbntyphpeidn_1","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\memory\\session\\pulse_2026-03-23 203040.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":933,"output":335,"cacheRead":11878,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":13146,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774312870031}}
{"type":"message","id":"3f2bd625","parentId":"1dee5ac2","timestamp":"2026-03-24T00:41:19.617Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_vbntyphpeidn_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"﻿# Pulse: 2026-03-23 203040\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: research/tic_classifier.py (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine the best concrete action to advance the goals.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals:\r\n1. Phase 0 and Phase 1 are marked COMPLETE\r\n2. The main pending work is the TIC Experiment (Temporal Invariance Compression)\r\n3. Next action items include:\r\n   - Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n   - Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n   - Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n   - Validate against success criteria (>70%, >60%)\r\n\r\nThe most concrete next step would be to start implementing the TIC classifier. I should:\r\n1. Look at the pulse log files to understand their structure\r\n2. Create an initial TIC classifier implementation\r\n\r\nLet me check what pulse log files exist and their format, then create the TIC classifier.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC experiment is blocked on implementing the classifier. The pulse logs in `logs/` contain the data needed to test the compression-causal duality hypothesis. I need to implement the TIC classifier and begin testing.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) classifier script that will analyze pulse logs, classify content as invariant/variant, and predict next-pulse content. This directly advances the Phase 1 advancement goal.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: #!/usr/bin/env pwsh\r\n# Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Classifier\r\n# Tests hypothesis: causal structure IS invariant structure\r\n# Success criteria: >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nparam(\r\n    [string]$LogsDir = \"logs\",\r\n    [string]$OutputFile = \"research/TIC_RESULTS.md\",\r\n    [int]$MinPulseLength = 100\r\n)\r\n\r\n$ErrorActionPreference = \"Stop\"\r\n\r\nfunction Get-PulseFiles {\r\n    Get-ChildItem -Path $LogsDir -Filter \"pulse_*.md\" | \r\n        Sort-Object LastWriteTime |\r\n        Select-Object -ExpandProperty FullName\r\n}\r\n\r\nfunction Extract-Content {\r\n    param([string]$FilePath)\r\n    \r\n    $content = Get-Content $FilePath -Raw\r\n    # Extract key sections\r\n    $observation = if ($content -match '(?s)### OBSERVATION\\s*\\n(.*?)(?=\\n###|\\z)') { $matches[1].Trim() } else { \"\" }\r\n    $action = if ($content -match '(?s)### ACTION\\s*\\n(.*?)(?=\\n###|\\z)') { $matches[1].Trim() } else { \"\" }\r\n    $mutation = if ($content -match '(?s)### MUTATION\\s*\\n(.*?)(?=```\\s*$|\\z)') { $matches[1].Trim() } else { \"\" }\r\n    \r\n    return @{\r\n        Observation = $observation\r\n        Action = $action\r\n        Mutation = $mutation\r\n        Raw = $content\r\n        FilePath = $FilePath\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\nfunction Get-Ngrams {\r\n    param([string]$Text, [int]$N = 3)\r\n    \r\n    $words = $Text -split '\\s+' | Where-Object { $_.Length -gt 3 }\r\n    if ($words.Count -lt $N) { return @() }\r\n    \r\n    $ngrams = @()\r\n    for ($i = 0; $i -le $words.Count - $N; $i++) {\r\n        $ngram = ($words[$i..($i + $N - 1)] -join \" \").ToLower()\r\n        $ngrams += $ngram\r\n    }\r\n    return $ngrams\r\n}\r\n\r\nfunction Find-Invariants {\r\n    param([array]$PulseContents)\r\n    \r\n    # Build n-gram frequency across all pulses\r\n    $allNgrams = @{}\r\n    foreach ($pulse in $PulseContents) {\r\n        $ngrams = Get-Ngrams -Text ($pulse.Observation + \" \" + $pulse.Action) -N 2\r\n        foreach ($ngram in $ngrams) {\r\n            $allNgrams[$ngram] = ($allNgrams[$ngram] ?? 0) + 1\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    # Invariants appear in >60% of pulses (adjusted by pulse count)\r\n    $totalPulses = $PulseContents.Count\r\n    $threshold = [Math]::Max(2, [int]($totalPulses * 0.6))\r\n    \r\n    $invariants = @{}\r\n    foreach ($ngram in $allNgrams.Keys) {\r\n        if ($allNgrams[$ngram] -ge $threshold) {\r\n            $invariants[$ngram] = $allNgrams[$ngram]\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    return $invariants\r\n}\r\n\r\nfunction Classify-Pulse {\r\n    param([object]$Pulse, [hashtable]$Invariants)\r\n    \r\n    $text = $Pulse.Observation + \" \" + $Pulse.Action\r\n    $ngrams = Get-Ngrams -Text $text -N 2\r\n    \r\n    $invariantCount = 0\r\n    $variantCount = 0\r\n    \r\n    foreach ($ngram in $ngrams) {\r\n        if ($Invariants.ContainsKey($ngram)) {\r\n            $invariantCount++\r\n        } else {\r\n            $variantCount++\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    $total = $invariantCount + $variantCount\r\n    if ($total -eq 0) {\r\n        return @{ Classification = \"UNKNOWN\"; InvariantRatio = 0; InvariantCount = 0; VariantCount = 0 }\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    $ratio = $invariantCount / $total\r\n    $classification = if ($ratio -gt 0.5) { \"INVARIANT\" } else { \"VARIANT\" }\r\n    \r\n    return @{\r\n       \n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-23 20:31:03\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774312879614}}
{"type":"message","id":"a590a922","parentId":"3f2bd625","timestamp":"2026-03-24T00:41:38.313Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have the pulse log content. Let me summarize the key findings:\n\n1. The pulse ran successfully at 20:40:42\n2. It found 7 files changed with 315 insertions and 104 deletions\n3. A new session log was created: `memory/session/pulse_2026-03-23 204042.md`\n4. One mutation was rejected (2026-03-23 203040.mutation moved to rejected)\n5. A new mutation was proposed: `mutations/proposed/2026-03-23 204042.mutation`\n6. The TIC experiment is the next priority but blocked on a working implementation\n\n\n7. The pulse script was cut off mid-file, so the full analysis is still loading\n\nI'm noticing the file listing showed `pulse_2026-03-23 203040.md` as the most recent, but the pulse output references creating `pulse_2026-03-23 204042.md` — these might be different files, or there's a timing issue with how the files were written. Looking at the mutation file contents, it appears the new TIC classifier script was successfully written to `sandbox/TIC/classifier.ps1` — the old_text was indeed \"(new file)\" as the mutation indicated, and the new script content matches what was proposed. The mutation was applied and committed to the master branch. Looking at the grep output more carefully, I see the mutation file is just showing the classifier implementation itself, which is the new file being created rather than a modification to an existing file. The \"old_text: (new file)\" notation confirms this is a fresh file, not an edit to something that already existed. The script was successfully written and committed as `master f62a59a`, creating both the new pulse session log and the TIC classifier script. Now I need to locate the most recent pulse log to verify the full scope of what was created in this cycle.","thinkingSignature":"4df972ae438fdf86c47d75462d527d9c44efedc27e78fac7d702509a6e07a7b5"},{"type":"text","text":"The exec output showed `pulse_2026-03-23 203040.md` as newest *before* the pulse ran. The pulse itself created `pulse_2026-03-23 204042.md`. Let me grab that one too for the complete picture.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_frmykv108a1b_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"powershell -Command \"Get-ChildItem 'C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\memory\\session\\' | Sort-Object LastWriteTime -Descending | Select-Object -First 1 -ExpandProperty FullName\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":2548,"output":529,"cacheRead":11878,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":14955,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774312879619}}
